When you run this program, it will prompt you to enter a valid BIN number as input. The program will then generate all possible credit card numbers by appending the remaining 10 digits, check each number using the Luhn algorithm, and keep track of the count of valid numbers. Optionally, you can uncomment the print statement to see all the valid card numbers as output.

Please note that the program will take a significant amount of time to complete since it enumerates all possible 6-digit combinations and checks their validity. The execution time will depend on your system's resources and the specific BIN provided.
